column28: One of my favorite aspects of this internship was the opportunity to apply what I’ve learned in a real-world setting. I particularly enjoyed the hands-on projects, which allowed me to develop both technical and professional skills. The mentorship and feedback from supervisors were incredibly valuable, they provided guidance while also giving me the freedom to take initiative. I also appreciated the team environment; collaborating with others helped me learn new perspectives and problem-solving approaches. Overall, I gained a deeper understanding of the field and strengthened my confidence in my abilities.
column29: While the internship was a great learning experience, I think it could be improved by providing a bit more structure at the beginning. For instance, an orientation or clearer overview of project expectations would have helped me get started more efficiently. Additionally, having more regular check-ins or opportunities to discuss progress would be useful for ensuring alignment and continued learning. Some of the provided materials felt a bit general, so tailoring resources more closely to specific projects could make them more helpful.

column28: The hands-on Flutter development experience was my favorite aspect. I particularly enjoyed working on real projects and learning from experienced mentors. The practical problem-solving activities were most helpful in building my technical skills. I learned new development techniques, debugging strategies, and gained valuable insights into professional workflows. The supportive team environment made the learning process enjoyable and productive.
column29:
Overall, the internship was a great learning experience. However, I believe a few areas could be enhanced. More structured onboarding materials or documentation would have helped me get started more quickly in the initial phase. Additionally, clearer task guidelines and expected deliverables would have reduced confusion during project assignments.
Regular check-ins or progress reviews could provide better guidance and ensure alignment with expectations. While the learning resources were helpful, having access to more advanced tutorials or case studies specific to our projects would have been beneficial. These improvements would make the internship even more effective for future participants.
